      "is_standard": "true",
      "mechanism": null,
      "name": "Lead",
      "notes": "Standard CRM-module entity. Leads convert into Account + Contact + Opportunity (configurable). Original lead is preserved with status values like New, Assigned, In Process, Converted, Recycled, Dead. The Account.originalLead linkOne field on the converted Account points back to the source Lead.",
      "system": "espocrm"
    },
    {
      "api_name": "contacts",
      "docs_url": "https://knowledge.hubspot.com/contacts/use-lifecycle-stages",
      "is_standard": "false",
      "mechanism": null,
      "name": "Contact (with lifecyclestage=lead)",
      "notes": "MAJOR DIVERGENCE. HubSpot has no separate Lead entity. Pre- qualification state is captured by the `lifecyclestage` property on Contact (values: subscriber, lead, marketingqualifiedlead, salesqualifiedlead, opportunity, customer, evangelist, other). Conversion is just a property update; no separate object swap. HubSpot Sales Hub Enterprise added a separate Leads object in 2024 but it's behind a subscription tier and the Contact-with-lifecyclestage pattern remains the dominant model.",
      "system": "hubspot"
    },
    {
      "api_name": "Lead",
      "docs_url": "https://developer.salesforce.com/docs/atlas.en-us.object_reference.meta/object_reference/sforce_api_objects_lead.htm",
      "is_standard": "true",
      "mechanism": null,
      "name": "Lead",
      "notes": "Standard object with an explicit Convert lifecycle. A Lead is created with name and company; when qualified, the Convert action creates Account + Contact + Opportunity records and marks the Lead as converted (IsConverted=true, ConvertedAccountId / ConvertedContactId / ConvertedOpportunityId populated). The Lead record persists for audit but is functionally retired.",
      "system": "salesforce"
    },
